 yale=Hike.create(user_id: admin.id, title: 'Mount Yale Summit Trail', city: 'Buena Vista', state: 'Colorado', difficulty: 5, length: 10, pet_friendly: true, directions: 'From the town of Buena Vista, head west from the stoplight( Main Street or 306),which turns to Cottonwood Pass, then go to the Denny Creek trailhead.', extra_info: 'From the fork, the trail is fairly easy up until around 13,000 feet. From here follow the switchbacks up to the saddle around 13,900. This area is steep and probably the most demanding part of the hike. Once you reach the saddle you have about 300 more feet of elevation gain which requires class 2 scrambling with options of class 3.')
 HikePhoto.create(hike_id: yale.id, img_url: 'https://cdn-assets.alltrails.com/uploads/photo/image/10085586/extra_large_2a656063a78eb0b73435c45333b53518.jpg', caption: 'Mount Yale')
