 sherman = Hike.create(user_id: admin.id, title: 'Mount Sherman', city: 'Leadville', state: 'Colorado', difficulty: 4, length: 5, pet_friendly: true, directions: 'To access this trail, take County Road 18 and, starting at the Leavick Site at around ten miles (16 km) in, there are numerous parking areas with signs. Depending on your car, you can choose to continue up the road, which gets more rugged as it goes. The road is rough, but doable if moving slowly. The hike itself begins at Fourmile Creek Trailhead.', extra_info: 'Mt. Sherman is one of the easiest 14ers and it is full of mining history. Do not attempt to climb the cornice blocking the trail. It’s safest to hike around it to avoid getting injured. As you approach the large abandoned mine, stay climber’s right and then traverse left across the more mild snowfield to gain the ridge.')
 HikePhoto.create(hike_id: sherman.id, img_url: 'https://cdn-assets.alltrails.com/uploads/photo/image/38315689/extra_large_5b6d535f9c28b926166ff273dc85fc2e.jpg', caption: 'Mount Sherman')
