 turq = Hike.create(user_id: admin.id, title: 'Turquoise Lake Trail', city: 'Leadville', state: 'Colorado', difficulty: 2, length: 11, pet_friendly: true, directions: 'From Leadville head south on Harrison Ave toward W 8th St. Turn right onto W 8th St, then in half a mile turn right onto James St. After that turn left onto McWenthy Dr. In 2.5 miles turn right onto County Rd 4, then follow that for 3 miles.', extra_info: 'Turquoise Lake Trail is a 11 mile moderately trafficked out and back trail located near Leadville, Colorado that features a lake and is good for all skill levels. The trail offers a number of activity options and is best used from April until September. If you go in the fall this is a great hike to see the leaves changing color. Dogs are also able to use this trail but must be kept on leash.')
