 vrain = Hike.create(user_id: admin.id, title: 'Saint Vrain Mountain Trail', city: 'Indian Peaks Wilderness', state: 'Colorado', difficulty: 5, length: 8, pet_friendly: false, directions: 'Take Highway 7 to Allenspark and take the Business Loop 7 (which goes through the middle of town) to find CR107. Take CR107 as it winds through the neighborhood for about 1.5 miles and it will turn into Forrest Road 116. Follow 116 for about 1/2 mile more and it will split into two (116.1 and 116.2) keep to the right. There is a sign indicating it is the St Vrain trailhead parking. Parking is small and limited.', extra_info: 'The trail starts in an aspen grove and rises upon a south facing slope in mixed aspens and pines. Shortly after entering the Indian Peaks Wilderness the trail parallels a creek. After a couple small switchbacks temporarily leave the creek, a big switchback carries you up from the stream to where you get your first views of the area. Traversing around the upper basin of the stream, the trail finally crosses the stream and leaves the pines and aspens for firs and spruces. Views out to the plains improve as the trail swings back north and then turns to reach treeline after a short steep switchback. The trail crosses the divide into the Wild Basin drainage and Rocky Mountain National Park with views of peaks defining the basin. After descending briefly into the forested saddle on the east side of St. Vrain Mountain, you leave the trail to climb to the summit. Some cairns define a few routes but there is little difficulty in almost any route chosen that avoids krumholz; in general, once above the trees you will probably travel near the park boundary, which is marked with flexible posts.')
 HikePhoto.create(hike_id: vrain.id, img_url: 'https://cdn-assets.alltrails.com/uploads/photo/image/11424425/extra_large_fb126d30ac075c1e0aeead2e7348ba30.jpg', caption: 'St. Vrain Mountain (L), and Meadow Mt. (R)')
 HikePhoto.create(hike_id: vrain.id, img_url: 'https://cdn-assets.alltrails.com/uploads/photo/image/39311403/extra_large_6c26ab39b923f81f2e01636b41a03ee1.jpg', caption: 'Saint Vrain Mountain Trail')
 HikePhoto.create(hike_id: vrain.id, img_url: 'https://cdn-assets.alltrails.com/uploads/photo/image/40744727/extra_large_c32f926cf049d5ee1a7aa0410f932b4e.jpg', caption: 'All the way up')

 devil= Hike.create(user_id: admin.id, title: 'Devils Thumb Pass and King Lake Trail', city: 'Indian Peaks Wilderness', state: 'Colorado', difficulty: 5, length: 17, pet_friendly: true, directions: 'Directions from Eldora: Travel west to the Hessie Townsite on CR #130', extra_info: 'Devils Thumb Pass and King Lake Trail can be a challenging day hike or a perfect multi day backpacking trip in the Indian Peaks Wilderness! This route is great for wildflowers in the spring and home to many moose and elk. Expect incredible views of the surrounding mountains once you get up to the Continental Divide. In the colder months, be sure to use proper gear such as microspikes, as this trail can get icy!')
