 joy = Hike.create(user_id: admin.id, title: 'Oh-Be-Joyful Trail', city: 'Crested Butte', state: 'Colorado', difficulty: 5, length: 14, pet_friendly: true, directions: 'Directions from Crested Butte: Travel a half mile north on Gothic Road to Slate River Road, Forest Road 734, and drive three and a half miles northwest to Oh-Be-Joyful Road', extra_info: 'This route is not open during the winter months due to snow. Trail begins at the Ob-Be-Joyful Trailhead and campground. There are several downed trees from avalanches that you will navigate around but pick up the trail easily. Once you reach the intersection of the Oh-Be-Joyful trail and Blue Lake trail, take a left and head toward Blue Lake. You will gain ~1,000 ft of elevation from this intersection to Blue Lake. There are dispersed camping sites available throughout the trail but space is limited at the lake.')
